    "description": "<strong>Sometimes Always Monsters is a narrative roleplaying life simulator filled with choices.</strong><br><br>You play a recently married author who joins a cross-country bus tour to promote your next upcoming novel. Along the way, you hear about vicious rumours claiming you're a total fraud.<br><br>As you journey through five unique cities, meet fans and critics alike, and make friends with your fellow busmates, it'll be your choices that help unravel the conspiracy laid against you.<br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/441440/extras/3e5f812a2995f0cca81c7c79b68835bd.avif?t=1729528132\" width=620 height=65 /></span><br><strong>Roleplay Creatively</strong> as you navigate the life of your character. In addition to countless dialogue choices, you'll decide how you want to live. Whether you like being a diligent workaholic, or prefer the route of a relaxed layabout,  the choice is entirely up to you.<br><br><strong>Import Save Files</strong> from <u>Always Sometimes Monsters</u> to continue your story, no matter how tragic or triumphant your ending may have been. Your entire continuity will be carried over.<br><br><strong>Build Relationships</strong> with your spouse, friends, and more. Learn how to manage the demands of various social relationships as you maintain a life in the spotlight, and reach for your goals.<br><br><strong>Decline Anything</strong> you don't want to do. Nearly all of the game's content is optional, including the entirety of the primary narrative. You're truly in control of the story, with a right to refusal.<br><br><strong><u>Mature Content Warning</u></strong><br><i>Always Sometimes Monsters deals with serious stuff, depending on your choices. Including strong language, racist, homophobic, and transphobic language, drug / alcohol use, nudity, violence, and extreme subject matter.</i>",
